description._content: "Hector Arthur Gee (10 November 1909 – 1987) was an Australian professional rugby league footballer of the 1930s, and '40s, playing at representative level for Australia (#167), British Empire XIII, and Dominion XIII, and at club level in Australia for Tivoli, and in England for Wigan, as a Stand-off/Five-eighth, or Scrum-half/Halfback, i.e. number 6, or 7." en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hector_Gee Format: Photograph Find more detailed information about this photographic collection: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/item/itemDetailPaged.aspx?itemID=52644 Search for more great images in the State Library's collections: acms.sl.nsw.gov.au/search/SimpleSearch.aspx From the collection of the State Library of New South Wales www.sl.nsw.gov.au
